children.subject: this semester, at first they didn't post webcasts until a week after the original lecture, and when people complained about that, they made attendance at lectures count for 2% of your final grade (but released webcasts immediately).
Don't skip 16A lectures, they're pretty serious about attendance
Also, I might be wrong but I don't think you are allowed to double book anymore.
How did you find out that 160 and ee 16a conflict next semester?

history.content:
I'm debating whether I should do this...

I really want to take 160 (make an app sounds fun, it's a group project that I can mention in interviews etc), but it conflicts with 16a. It's my fifth semester here and I should take 16a (was going to take it this semester but conflicts with 170), and next semester it conflicts with 160.... There is a chance I'll be graduating in 3 years (most likely 3.5) so I don't want to push 16a back further. 

How bad is it to skip half of the 16a lectures? Is there webcast? How's the workload for both classes like? (I'm taken all lower-divs, 168, 170, 186, 188)

I'll most likely take 189 and some H/SS class with these classes.
